  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div xml:id="AN141.2-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">piriviṭai yāṟṟāḷeṉak kavaṉṟa tōḻikkuk kiḻatti colliyatu.
            aṟumīṉeṉṟa turōkaṇimīṉ.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <l>1. What SHE said to the confidante who was anxious she would not have the strength in the time of separation.</l>
            <l>2. What SHE said to the confidante who was anxious she would not have the strength.</l>
            </p>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="AN141.2">
            <lg type="edition">
                <l>amma vāḻi tōḻi kaimmikak</l>
                <l>kaṉavuṅ kaṅku <supplied>lē</supplied>tiṟōṉṟi naṉavum</l>
                <l>puṉaiviṉai nalliṟ puḷḷum pāṅkiṉa</l>
                <l>neñcu naṉipukaṉ ṟuṟaiyu meñcā</l>
                <l>tulakutoḻi lulantu nāñci ṟuñca</l>
                <l>maḻaikā ṉīṅkiya māka vicumpiṟ</l>
                <l>kuṟumuyaṉ maṟuniṟaṅ kiḷara matiniṟain</l>
                <l>taṟumīṉ cēru makaliru ṇaṭunāṇ</l>
                <l>maṟukuviḷak kuṟuttu mālai tūkkip</l>
                <l>paḻaviṟaṉ mūtūrp palaruṭaṉ ṟuvaṉṟi</l>
                <l>viḻavuḷ yāvarum varukati<supplied>l</supplied> lamma</l>
                <l>tuvarap puṉaintu tūmalar kañlit</l>
                <l>takara nāṟun taṇṇaṟuṅ katuppiṟ</l>
                <l>putumaṇa makaṭūu vayiṉiya kaṭina<supplied>ka</supplied>rp</l>
                <l>palkō ṭaṭuppiṟ pālulai yirīik</l>
                <l>kūḻaik kūntaṟ kuṟuntoṭi makaḷir</l>
                <l>peruñcey nelliṉ vāṅkukatir murittup</l>
                <l>pācava liṭikku miruṅkā ḻulakkaik</l>
                <l>kaṭiti<supplied>ṭi</supplied> verī<supplied>i</supplied>ya kamañcūl veṇkuruku</l>
                <l>tīṅkulai vāḻai yōṅkumaṭa lirātu</l>
                <l>neṭuṅkāṉ marāttuk kuṟumpaṟai payiṟṟuñ</l>
                <l>celkuṭi niṟutta perumpeyark karikāl</l>
                <l>velpōrc cōḻa ṉiṭaiyāṟ ṟaṉṉa</l>
                <l>nallicai veṟukkai tarumār palpoṟip</l>
                <l>pulikkē ḻuṟṟa pūvuṭaip peruñciṉai</l>
                <l>naranta naṟumpū nāṇmala rutirak</l>
                <l>kalaipāyn tukaḷuṅ kalcēr vēṅkait</l>
                <l>tēṅkamaḻ neṭuvaraip piṟaṅkiya</l>
                <l>vēṅkaṭa veṟpiṟ curamiṟan tōrē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <l>Alas, oh friend. While at night</l>
                <l>[my] dreams appear very strange and when awake the birds</l>
                <l>are close to the good house of artful work[manship], (1-3)</l>
                <l>[my] heart keeps much rejoicing. While without exception (4)</l>
                <l>the works of the world have died down [and] the ploughs sleep, (5)</l>
                <l>at midnight in the vast darkness when the moon becomes full,</l>
                <l>so that that dirty colour of the small hare shines, [and] joins the six stars</l>
                <l>in the vast sky which clouds [and] wind have left, (6-8)</l>
                <l>would that everyone came to the festival, (11)</l>
                <l>many together filling up the old village of ancient victories,</l> 
                <l>kindling lamps in the streets, hanging up garlands (9f.)</l>
                <l>– he [included] who, in order to give famous riches, (24a-c)</l>
                <l rend="indent4">like Iṭaiyāṟu, [the place] of the Cōḻa of victorious battle,</l>
                <l rend="indent4">Karikāl with great name who stopped the clans on the move(?), (22f.)</l>
                <l rend="indent4">where the fully pregnant white ibises, that are frightened by the thunder that is harsh</l>
                <l rend="indent4">of the large hard pestles that pound fresh rice,</l>
                <l rend="indent4">breaking the bowing ears of paddy from the big fields,</l>
                <l rend="indent4">[used by] women with small bangles [and] short tresses</l>
                <l rend="indent4">after setting pots with milk on ovens with many curves, (15)</l>
                <l rend="indent4">[their] hair cool [and] fragrant, scented with unguent</l>
                <l rend="indent4">[and] dense with pure blossoms, done up by dividing [it into strands],</l>
                <l rend="indent4">no [longer] perch on the high fronds of the plantain tree with sweet [fruit] bunches</l>
                <l rend="indent4">repeat [their] short flights on the long-trunked Kadamba trees, (12-21)</l>
                <l>has gone to traverse the desert of the Vēṅkaṭam mountains (29)</l>
                <l>that glisten with high peaks fragrant with the honey</l>
                <l>of kino trees joining the stones where monkeys leap [and] jump</l>
                <l>when, from the big branches that possess flowers that have the lustre of the tiger with many dots,</l>
                <l>day[-fresh] blossoms drop on the fragrant flowers of the bitter orange. (24d-28)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
